    <text>
        <body>
            
            <div1 type="letter">
                
                <pb facs="nei.j4c.64.2" />
                
                <fw type="curatorial">2</fw>
                
                <opener>
                    <dateline>
                        5835 Vine Street
                        Lincoln, Nebraska 68505
                        September 22, 1972
                    </dateline>
                    
                    <address>
                        <addrLine>Mr. Brent A. Warren</addrLine>
                        <addrLine>5420 Ervin Street</addrLine>
                        <addrLine>Lincoln, Nebraska 68504</addrLine>
                    </address>
                    
                    <salute>Dear Mr. Warren:</salute>
                </opener>
                <p>I have just read your generous letter of August 12, 1972, regarding my work and the Dick Cavett program. I thank you for your kindly remarks.</p>
                
                <p>Naturally I am interested in the project you have in mind and if I can be of any service to you, I shall be glad. Perhaps you might want to come to my home here for a little talk. If so, you might phone and make an appointment with Mrs. Young, who manages my affairs.</p>
                <closer>
                    <salute>With all kind thoughts,</salute>
                    
                    <signed>John G. Neihardt</signed>
                    
                    <note>JGN:nh</note>
                </closer>
                
                <postscript>
                    <p>The t<del>l<unclear>e</unclear></del><add>el</add>ephohne number is 466-9573.</p>
                </postscript>
                
            </div1>
